Here are both approaches for navigating from `ProductListPage` to `ProductDetailsPage`:

## 1. Register the route

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

## 2. Navigate from ProductListPage

**Approach A — String query parameter (product ID only):**

```csharp
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

**Approach B — Pass the full object via `ShellNavigationQueryParameters`:**

```csharp
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

## 3. Receive data with IQueryAttributable on the ViewModel

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product { get => _product; set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from service if needed
        }

        // Approach B: full object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

## Key points

| | Query string | ShellNavigationQueryParameters |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | Strings only | Any object |
| **URI visible** | Yes (`?productId=42`) | No |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, deep links | Complex objects, avoiding re-fetch |

Always `await` `GoToAsync` — fire-and-forget causes race conditions. Set the ViewModel as `BindingContext` on `ProductDetailsPage` (ideally via DI) so `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called automatically by Shell.
